00:04:49.980 --> 00:04:51.440
The place that you first go.

00:04:51.440 --> 00:04:52.910
We don't have that concept.

00:04:52.910 --> 00:04:55.900
So you go to a page,
you go to an app.

00:04:55.900 --> 00:04:58.400
You leave, you come back, and
you're like at the same place.

00:04:58.400 --> 00:04:59.983
That might be good,
that might be bad.

00:04:59.983 --> 00:05:01.620
When you install
an app, usually you

00:05:01.620 --> 00:05:04.872
want a place to go
where you start from.

00:05:04.872 --> 00:05:06.330
So I'm really trying
to rush these.

00:05:06.330 --> 00:05:08.990
Navigational
boundaries-- so when

00:05:08.990 --> 00:05:10.630
you install an app
like a native app,

00:05:10.630 --> 00:05:12.672
it has a starting point
and an ending point.

00:05:12.672 --> 00:05:14.880
And you know when you jump
from one app to the other.

00:05:14.880 --> 00:05:16.230
On the web, there
isn't that concept.

00:05:16.230 --> 00:05:17.813
We don't have a
concept of boundaries.

00:05:17.813 --> 00:05:21.420
You follow links, and if
those links look the same,

00:05:21.420 --> 00:05:23.920
essentially in the same app--
you can be at Google.com

00:05:23.920 --> 00:05:25.432
and bounce from one
app to the other

00:05:25.432 --> 00:05:27.140
and you wouldn't even
know where you are.

00:05:27.140 --> 00:05:31.100
So the only cues that
we have are visual cues.

00:05:31.100 --> 00:05:34.180
In native apps you actually
have actual boundaries.

00:05:34.180 --> 00:05:38.410
They'll call them physical
boundaries that prevent you

00:05:38.410 --> 00:05:41.810
from going from one
place to another.

00:05:41.810 --> 00:05:44.220
And the visual cues
are very evident.

00:05:44.220 --> 00:05:46.932
And they're not
there on the web,

00:05:46.932 --> 00:05:48.390
or at least in the
installable web,

00:05:48.390 --> 00:05:52.720
particularly people who've
tried to build for iOS.

00:05:52.720 --> 00:05:54.590
